title Attention Circle Detector — Architecture & Functionality

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam dpi 150
skinparam roundcorner 8
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam class {
  BackgroundColor #F7FAFF
  BorderColor #3B6EA5
  ArrowColor #3B6EA5
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #FFF7E0
  BorderColor #C9A227
}
legend left
  Task: given a set of 2D points (x, y, grayscale c), the model predicts —
  for every point independently — a vector to the circle's centre and the
  probability that the point lies inside the circle.
endlegend

' ===================== MODEL =====================
package "model.py" {
  class PositionalEncoding {
    +pe : buffer [max_len, d_model]
    +forward(x) : x + positional
  }
  class AttentionCircleDetector {
    +d_model : int
    +input_embedding : Linear(3 -> d_model)
    +pos_encoder : PositionalEncoding
    +transformer_encoder : TransformerEncoder
    +vector_head : Linear(d_model -> 2)
    +probability_head : Linear(d_model -> 1) + Sigmoid
    --
    +forward(src) : (vectors, probs, feats)
    +loss_function(v', p', v, y) : total_loss
  }
  class "nn.Module" as NNModule <<torch>>
}

PositionalEncoding --|> NNModule
AttentionCircleDetector --|> NNModule
AttentionCircleDetector *-- PositionalEncoding : composes

note right of AttentionCircleDetector
  **Forward pass** (batch B, N points, 3 features)
  (B,N,3)
   -> Linear embed  x  sqrt(d_model)
   -> + sinusoidal positional encoding
   -> TransformerEncoder (nhead, num_layers)
   -> per-point feature (B,N,d_model)
   -> vector_head  -> (B,N,2)  vector point->centre
   -> probability_head -> (B,N,1) P(inside)
  Per-point heads => order-equivariant output;
  attention lets points "vote" on the shared circle.
end note

note bottom of AttentionCircleDetector
  **Loss function**  L = ||v' - v||^2  - y·log p' - (1-y)·log(1-p')
  • term 1: squared error of the predicted centre vector (regression)
  • term 2: binary cross-entropy of inside/outside (classification)
  Implemented as: mean over points of (vector MSE) + (BCE), then summed.
  eps=1e-9 guards log(0).
end note

' ===================== CONFIG =====================
package "run_config.py" {
  class RunConfig <<dataclass frozen>> {
    +input_dim = 3
    +d_model = 120
    +nhead = 8
    +num_encoder_layers = 6
    +dim_feedforward = 512
    +dropout = 0.1
    +max_seq_len, num_points, epochs
    +batch_size, lr
    +noise, noise_std, clutter, clutter_fraction
  }
  class "run_config (helpers)" as RunCfgMod <<module>> {
    +validate_run_config(cfg)
    +build_model(cfg) : AttentionCircleDetector
    +run_dir(root, cfg) / run_name(cfg)
    +save_config / load_config
    +model/metrics/config/architecture_path_for_run
  }
}

RunCfgMod ..> RunConfig : reads/validates
RunCfgMod ..> AttentionCircleDetector : build_model() constructs

note right of RunConfig
  **d_model divisibility rule**
  d_model must be divisible by nhead (multi-head
  attention splits d_model into nhead slices) and
  even (positional encoding). 120 works for heads
  1-6 & 8, but NOT 7 -> sweep bumps heads=7 to 126.
  validate_run_config() enforces this.
end note

' ===================== DATA =====================
package "data_generator.py" {
  class "data_generator" as DataGen <<module>> {
    +generate_circle_data(num_points, img_size=(-0.5,0.5), ...)
    ..returns..
    points[N,3], vectors[N,2], labels[N], (centre, r)
    --
    +visualize_data(points, labels, circle)
  }
}

note bottom of DataGen
  **Synthetic data spec**
  • points x,y ~ U(-0.5, 0.5); plane = [-0.5,0.5]^2
  • radius ~ U(0.1, 0.25): min fixed 0.1, max = 0.5·width/2,
    centre constrained so the circle is fully inside
  • feature c = grayscale (circle vs background intensity)
  • optional Gaussian noise on c and random "clutter" points
  • ground truth per point: vector to centre + inside/outside label
  A FRESH random scene is drawn every batch (infinite stream,
  no fixed dataset).
end note

' ===================== TRAIN =====================
package "train.py" {
  class "train" as TrainMod <<module>> {
    +main() : training loop
    +generate_visualizations(model, ...)
    +format_eta(seconds)
  }
}

TrainMod ..> RunCfgMod : build_model, save_config
TrainMod ..> DataGen : generate_circle_data (per epoch)
TrainMod ..> AttentionCircleDetector : forward + loss_function + Adam

note right of TrainMod
  **Training loop**
  for each epoch: draw fresh batch -> forward -> loss
  -> backward -> Adam.step(). Keeps a deque of the last
  100 epoch losses; every 100 epochs records both
  loss_avg and loss_min for that window.
  **Outputs per run dir:** attention_circle_detector.pth,
  config.json, metrics.json (incl. training_summaries),
  architecture.txt, visualizations/*.png
end note

' ===================== SWEEP =====================
package "sweep_models.py" {
  class "sweep_models" as SweepMod <<module>> {
    +run_sweep(args)
    +resolve_d_model(base, nhead) : valid d_model
  }
}

SweepMod ..> TrainMod : subprocess per (layers, heads)

note right of SweepMod
  **Grid sweep + resume**
  Cartesian product of layers x heads. One `python train.py`
  subprocess per cell. resolve_d_model() picks the nearest
  even multiple of nhead >= base (heads=7 -> 126).
  --skip-existing skips cells that already have metrics.json
  (safe to re-run / resume); a failed cell is logged and the
  sweep continues instead of aborting.
end note

' ===================== EVALUATE =====================
package "evaluate.py" {
  class "evaluate" as EvalMod <<module>> {
    +evaluate_model(run_dir, visualize, num_examples, ...)
    +save_prediction_visualizations(model, ...)
    +_save_prediction_plot(...)
  }
}

EvalMod ..> RunCfgMod : load_config, build_model
EvalMod ..> DataGen : generate_circle_data
EvalMod ..> AttentionCircleDetector : inference + loss

note bottom of EvalMod
  **Evaluation & visual check**
  Loads a trained run, computes test loss on a fixed-seed set,
  and (--visualize) saves N annotated plots with per-example
  metrics: centre-localisation error, vector MSE, classification
  accuracy. Estimated centre = mean(point + predicted vector).
end note

' ===================== ANALYSIS =====================
package "analysis/generate_heatmap.py" {
  class "generate_heatmap" as HeatMod <<module>> {
    +collect_heatmap_data(run_root, metric)
    +save_heatmap(...) / save_summary_json(...)
    +RunRecord <<dataclass>>
  }
}

HeatMod ..> TrainMod : reads metrics.json produced by runs

note right of HeatMod
  **Heatmaps (layers x heads)**
  Metrics: final_epoch_loss, last_window_loss_min
  (min of last 100 epochs), last_window_loss_avg.
  Outputs <metric>_heatmap.png + .json summary.
end note

@enduml
